## Context

Part of the actions-extraction refactor. Plan: `.claude/plans/2026-04-27-actions-extraction.md` (Phase 7f). Last and largest caller migration — exercises every bulk mode (overdue, project, focus, inbox).

Actions.tsx is the central component used for /today (alongside TodayLayout for the redesign), /inbox, /tomorrow, /upcoming, project pages, and the Notion-unassigned filter. It conditionally enables 4 different bulk modes depending on viewName/projectId.

## Task

### File: `src/app/_components/Actions.tsx`

1. Line 4: change `import { ActionList } from './ActionList';` → `import { ActionsList } from './actions/ActionsList';`

2. Add import: `import type { Action } from '~/lib/actions/types';` (new, near other type imports)
3. Add import: `import type { BulkActionDef } from './actions/components/BulkEditToolbar';` (new)

4. Add a memoized `bulkActions` array near the other useMemos (e.g. after `schedulingSuggestionsMap`):
   ```tsx
   const bulkActions = useMemo<BulkActionDef[]>(() => {
     const list: BulkActionDef[] = [];
     if (projectId) {
       // Project view: assign-to-different-project + delete
       list.push({ kind: 'assignProject', onAssign: handleProjectBulkAssignProject });
       list.push({ kind: 'delete', onDelete: handleProjectBulkDelete });
     } else if (isFocusView(viewName)) {
       // Today/this-week/this-month/tomorrow: reschedule + delete
       list.push({ kind: 'reschedule', onReschedule: handleFocusBulkReschedule });
       list.push({ kind: 'delete', onDelete: handleFocusBulkDelete });
     } else if (viewName.toLowerCase() === 'inbox') {
       // Inbox: schedule (=reschedule) + assign-to-project + delete
       list.push({ kind: 'reschedule', onReschedule: handleInboxBulkSchedule });
       list.push({ kind: 'assignProject', onAssign: handleInboxBulkAssignProject });
       list.push({ kind: 'delete', onDelete: (ids) => { void handleInboxBulkDelete(ids); } });
     }
     // Overdue handlers always available across all non-project views
     // (in old ActionList, overdue had its own bulk-edit toggle inside the Overdue accordion;
     // in the new ActionsList, the Overdue section reuses the same bulkActions config — verify
     // that the section UI surfaces them on the Overdue subset)
     if (!projectId) {
       list.push({ kind: 'reschedule', onReschedule: handleOverdueBulkReschedule });
     }
     return list;
   }, [projectId, viewName, handleProjectBulkAssignProject, handleProjectBulkDelete, handleFocusBulkReschedule, handleFocusBulkDelete, handleInboxBulkSchedule, handleInboxBulkAssignProject, handleInboxBulkDelete, handleOverdueBulkReschedule]);
   ```

   IMPORTANT: review whether Actions.tsx should also expose Overdue bulk `delete` (handleOverdueBulkAction with 'delete') — old ActionList had `onOverdueBulkAction` for delete on the Overdue accordion. Add it if needed:
   ```tsx
   list.push({ kind: 'delete', onDelete: (ids) => handleOverdueBulkAction('delete', ids) });
   ```

5. Lines 1098-1126 region: replace the entire `<ActionList ... />` block with:
   ```tsx
   <ActionsList
     viewName={showNotionUnassigned ? "notion-unassigned" : viewName}
     actions={(filteredActions ?? []) as Action[]}
     showProject={!projectId}
     bulkActions={bulkActions}
     workspaceProjects={projectsQuery.data?.map(p => ({ id: p.id, name: p.name })) ?? []}
     schedulingSuggestions={schedulingSuggestionsMap}
     schedulingSuggestionsLoading={schedulingSuggestionsQuery.isLoading}
     onApplySchedulingSuggestion={handleApplySchedulingSuggestion}
     onDismissSchedulingSuggestion={handleDismissSchedulingSuggestion}
     isLoading={projectId ? projectActionsQuery.isLoading : allActionsQuery.isLoading}
     deepLinkActionId={detailedEnabled ? null : actionIdFromUrl}
     onActionOpen={handleActionOpen}
     onActionClose={clearActionId}
   />
   ```

6. Drop the now-unused `_schedulingSuggestionsError`, `_calendarConnected`, `applyingSuggestionId` from props passed to the new component (they were prefixed with underscore because they were already unused by ActionList).

7. Note: this caller does NOT use `onTagClick` (the tag filter is owned by Actions.tsx itself via internal state and the MultiSelect at line 947+). Do not pass `onTagClick` here.

8. Verify Actions.tsx still renders correctly when viewName='today' (now coexists with TodayLayout's /today rendering — DoPageContent.tsx routes to TodayLayout for the today filter and to Actions for tomorrow/upcoming, per Phase 6 changes).

## Files

- `src/app/_components/Actions.tsx` — modify: import swap; add bulkActions useMemo; rewrite ActionList JSX block; type the actions prop properly
- `src/lib/actions/types.ts` — read: confirm Action export
- `src/app/_components/actions/components/BulkEditToolbar.tsx` — read: confirm BulkActionDef export

## Dependencies

- Depends on: bead exponential-xc02 (Phase 5) — needs ActionsList shell. Migrating last because this caller has the highest test surface.

## Acceptance Criteria

1. `grep -n 'ActionList' src/app/_components/Actions.tsx` returns ZERO matches (only ActionsList).
2. `grep -n 'ActionsList' src/app/_components/Actions.tsx` returns the import + JSX usage.
3. `grep -n 'enableBulkEditFor' src/app/_components/Actions.tsx` returns ZERO.
4. `npm run check` passes.
5. `npm run test` passes.
6. `npm run test:integration` passes.
7. `npm run build` passes.
8. Manual /actions: bulk delete + reschedule (overdue) + delete still work; daily-plan badge fires.
9. Manual /inbox: bulk schedule + delete + assign-to-project all work.
10. Manual /tomorrow + /upcoming: bulk reschedule + delete still work (focus view).
11. Manual on a project page: bulk delete + assign-to-different-project still work; kanban toggle still works.
12. Manual: AI scheduling suggestions panel still appears for overdue actions when enabled.
13. Manual: Notion-unassigned filter still works (`showNotionUnassigned` toggle); tag filter still works.

## Context

Part of the actions-extraction refactor. Plan: `.claude/plans/2026-04-27-actions-extraction.md` (Phase 7e).

ViewBoard is the workspace-wide saved-views board with kanban/list segmented control. The list branch is the only caller using `enableBulkEditForAll` AND the only caller passing `onTagClick`. Also passes deepLinkActionId/onActionOpen/onActionClose.

## Task

### File: `src/app/_components/views/ViewBoard.tsx`

1. Line 35: change `import { ActionList } from "../ActionList";` → `import { ActionsList } from "../actions/ActionsList";`

2. Lines 742-755 region: replace
   ```tsx
   <ActionList
     viewName="actions"
     actions={(actions ?? []) as any}
     showProject={true}
     enableBulkEditForAll={true}
     onAllBulkDelete={handleBulkDelete}
     onAllBulkReschedule={handleBulkReschedule}
     onAllBulkAssignProject={handleBulkAssignProject}
     isLoading={isLoading}
     deepLinkActionId={deepLinkActionId}
     onActionOpen={onActionOpen}
     onActionClose={onActionClose}
     onTagClick={handleTagClick}
   />
   ```
   with
   ```tsx
   <ActionsList
     viewName="actions"
     actions={(actions ?? []) as Action[]}
     showProject
     bulkActions={[
       { kind: 'reschedule', onReschedule: handleBulkReschedule },
       { kind: 'delete', onDelete: handleBulkDelete },
       { kind: 'assignProject', onAssign: handleBulkAssignProject },
     ]}
     workspaceProjects={projectsQuery.data?.map(p => ({ id: p.id, name: p.name })) ?? []}
     isLoading={isLoading}
     deepLinkActionId={deepLinkActionId}
     onActionOpen={onActionOpen}
     onActionClose={onActionClose}
     onTagClick={handleTagClick}
   />
   ```

3. Add import: `import type { Action } from "~/lib/actions/types";` at the top of the file (replaces the `as any` cast).

4. Confirm a `projectsQuery` (or equivalent) exists in the file to source workspaceProjects; if not, add `const projectsQuery = api.project.getAll.useQuery({ workspaceId: workspace?.id }, { enabled: !!workspace });` near the existing queries.

